The paper is about a new approach to approximate query processing in databases, which involves learning from past query answers to improve the accuracy and speed of future queries. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on database systems and query processing, cs.DB is the most likely primary category, followed by cs.AI and cs.LG for the machine learning aspects.
